Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a drab-coloured pottery wine-jar, the exterior is covered with a light-brown slip and faint traces of two lines of black-painted hieratic text identifying the contents as wine of year 12 from the western Delta river branch.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393456) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393456)
